    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Thermostat</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Always fill the cooling system with the same type of coolant that was drained from the system. Do
                    not mix coolant types.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drain the cooling system. For additional information, refer to Cooling System Draining,
                Filling and Bleeding in this section.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Use care when removing the radiator hose band clamp or damage to the radiator hose can occur.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Carefully remove the clamp and disconnect the upper radiator hose.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0303008" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020147.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 2 stud bolts and the thermostat assembly.</para>
            <para>&#8226; Remove and discard the O-ring seal.</para>
            <para>&#8226; To install, tighten to 22 Nm (16 lb-ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0303009" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020089.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To install, reverse the removal procedure.</para>
            <para>&#8226; Install a new O-ring seal on the thermostat assembly.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
